<p>
@HI{{ga}} can be used in place @HI{{@EM{{noni}}}} although it is a weaker disjunctive. However, it is also free of the restrictions that apply to @HI{{@EM{{noni}}}}. The clause
that precedes @HI{{ga}} may be in the polite style if the main clause is also in the polite style, whereas the clause preceding @HI{{@EM{{noni}}}} is always in the plain style.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{keredo(mo)}}, and not @HI{{@EM{{noni}}}}, must be used when:
